<s> Under the topic of "Refreshing Locks", it hints that Client may include a Timeout header.  </s>
<s> But, Depth header has not being mentioned.  </s>
<s> Under the topic of "Depth and Locking", it discussed what will happen if "Depth" header is specified for creating a new lock.  </s>
<s> But, nothing was mentioned on what's its implication on a lock refreshing command.  </s>
<s> Should "bis" document clarify this?  </s>
<s> Thx, -Stanley  </s>
<s> Possibly.  </s>
<s> In general, methods should ignore unknown headers.  </s>
<s> In this particular  </s>
<s> case of course, the Depth header *is* used for LOCK (just only when creating new locks).  </s>
<s> So the options for LOCK refresh are:  </s>
<s> 1) server MUST respect Depth header, possibly changing the lock scope  </s>
<s> 2) server MAY respect Depth header, possibly changing the lock scope 3) server SHOULD ignore Depth header 4) server MUST ignore Depth header  </s>
<s> As 4) is what currently everybody seems to implement, I'd propose to  </s>
<s> choose that interpretration and clarify in RFC2518bis.  </s>
<s> Julian  </s>
<s> I agree with Julian that option 4 is probably best.  </s>
